csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 9:10 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Support the Druids</span><hr size=1> There may be some animosity, but ...<br>
<br>
There is a shortage of healers at the high end game.  Tanks feel it, damage dealers feel it.  Slowers feel it less, because all slowers except for one have at least 1 other &quot;best of job&quot; group role.<br>
<br>
If druids gained the ability to act as a primary healer in a group (and that means death mitigation as well as healing) the grouping situation for other classes would improve.<br>
<br>
The balance problem between priests is a thorny issue, but the game needs more healers.<br>
<br>
There are 9 good damage dealers at L 65 (wiz mag nec dru enc bst mnk rog rng).  You want as many of these as you can fit.<br>
<br>
There are 7 I'd-invite-you-for-buffs buffers at L 65 (enc bard cle dru shm nec(!) bst).  More than a handful of these is suboptimal, and their use is sometimes situational.<br>
<br>
There are 4 good slowing classes at L 65 (bard, shaman, enchanter, beastlord).  A group needs 1 slower, excess usually does another job.<br>
<br>
There are 3 good tank classes at L 65 (war pal shd).  A group needs 1 tank, excess is usually suboptimal.<br>
<br>
There is 1 good healing class at L 65.  A group needs 1 healer.<br>
