I'm tired of watching guildmates go LFG for days.  It should be &quot;grab a healer, a slower, a tank, and 3 damage dealers&quot; and go to town.  Right now it is:<br>
Grab a cleric, a tank, a slower, and 3 damage dealers<br>
OR grab 2 druids, a tank, a slower, 1 damage dealer, and a paladin<br>
OR grab 1 druid, a buff tank, a slower, 2 damage dealers, and a paladin<br>
OR drop the paladin and go to places where there are 5 other clerics in zone, or you can bring a 2 box cleric.<br>
OR hunt in areas with mobs trivial to an equivilent group with a cleric.<br>
<br>
2 druids can replace a cleric in a CHeal chain, using twice as many people, generating twice as much lag, and requiring twice as much loot and keys to gear up.  Oh baby, can we recruit more druids for their amazing raiding abilities!  20 rangers (chloro power!) can replace a cleric as well you know.<br>
<br>
The 2nd and 3rd best healers in the game are half as good as the best healer.  Every other healer is support compared to those 3.<br>
<br>
There are 3 classes who can rez, one twice as good (1.75 to 2.5 times less xp lost) as the others.<br>
<br>
Would it be balanced if wizards lost teleporting and snare, and had twice the DPS of any other class in the game?  No.<br>
<br>
The 3rd best haste class is 88% as good as the best haste class.<br>
The 8th best damage dealer is very close (66% to 75% I'd say) to the best damage dealer.  Who the best damage dealer is is a matter of arguement and situation!<br>
The 3rd best tank is competative with the best tank outside MT on raids.<br>
The 3rd best slower is 71%+ as good as the best slower (BST vs Shaman).<br>
<br>
The 2nd best healer is half as good as the best healer.  The 3rd best healer is between half and a quarter as good as the best healer.  The 4th best healer is a paladin.<br>
<br>
Like I said, you may hate druids, or think they have too much.  But, the game needs more classes with better healing.  And clerics need more width.<br>
